<div class="page-article__content-section" id="alerts">
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <div class="content-section__header">
      <h2 class="title">Alerts</h2>
      <p class="text--large">Oh no! Did you break something?</p>
      <p class="text">We highly doubt it, but this would be a good time to let the user know something went wrong. Alerts, should be used when the user needs instant feedback on an action they preformed. They are helpful when a user deletes a module or when they have successfully saved or created something new. Below you will find three types of alerts and how to best use them in the interface.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <% data.components_alerts.alerts.each do |a| %>
      <figure aria-hidden="true" class="alert--<%= a.type %> toggle-parent">
        <h5 class="alert__text"><%= a.text %></h5>
        <% link_to '#', class: 'alert__trigger' do %>
          <%= inline_svg("icons/close-icon.svg", class: "alert__icon alert__icon--close toggle-element") %>
        <% end %>
      </figure><br/>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <h4 class="content-section__label">Sample Code</h4>
<% code("html") do %>
  <figure aria-hidden="true" class="alert--alpha">
    <h5 class="alert__text">High fives! You have successfully updated the module.</h5>
    <a class="alert__trigger" href="#">
      <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="alert__icon alert__icon--close"><title>close-icon</title>
        <path d="M11.446 10L20 18.554 18.553 20 10 11.446 1.446 20 0 18.554 8.553 10 0 1.446 1.446 0 10 8.554 18.553 0 20 1.446" fill="#60A246" fill-rule="evenodd" id="app-icon"></path>
      </svg>
      
    </a>
  </figure>
<% end %><br/>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <h4 class="content-section__label">HTML Guidelines</h4>
    <p>This table gives you a quick overview of the CSS classes that can be applied to create alerts.</p>
    <table class="table">
      <thead class="table__header">
        <th class="table__header-item">Class Name</th>
        <th class="table__header-item">Usage</th>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="table__body">
        <tr>
          <td class="table__body-item" style="width:30%">.alert--[type]</td>
          <td class="table__body-item">This should be applied to the element you are styling to look like an alert. It provides the correct styles for the message being returned. The class name should change based on the type of alert being displayed. <% code("html") do %><figure class="alert--alpha"></figure><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="table__body-item" style="width:30%">[aria-hidden="true"]</td>
          <td class="table__body-item">Set this on the alert when it is hidden from the view.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="table__body-item" style="width:30%">[aria-hidden="false"]</td>
          <td class="table__body-item">Set this on the alert when it is visible in the view.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>